The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks (ANN) for classification problems and proposes a novel method for improving their performance by preprocessing the raw data. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS). Given the focus on ANN and classification, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of PCA and eigenvalues suggests a potential focus on dimensionality reduction and feature selection, which could also be relevant to cs.NE, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
